Despite the Constitutional Court pronouncing the former president must testify before the Zondo Commission, he’s still defiant. It will be interesting to see what the judicial system will do about this contempt. I’m waiting with so much curiosity to see what action will be taken. If he’s let of the hook, then surely it will indicate some people are above the law. This will again portray our judicial system as a mockery. Letter by LeAlbert Kiviet, Emdeni South